 long-format\ntibble with columns `chr, start, ..., metric, value, sample`). Concatenate them\nand save to `output/df_mku_split.rds`. Then pivot wider on `metric`, compute\n`mCpG = numCs / coverage` (dropping `coverage==0`), group by `(sample, chr)`\nand write the mean mCpG per group to `output/mean_mcpg_split.tsv` via\n`readr::write_tsv`.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/mean_mcpg_split.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: mean_mcpg_split.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"grp1__a1.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp1__a1.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"grp1__a2.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp1__a2.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"grp1__a3.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp1__a3.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"grp1_mku.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp1_mku.rds\"\n    },\n    \"grp2__b1.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp2__b1.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"grp2__b2.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp2__b2.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"grp2__b3.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp2__b3.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"grp2_mku.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp2_mku.rds\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/mean_mcpg_split.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_vHfFxxjEUPV3DubDJmV0eohg", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the RDS files from the input directory.\\n2. Concatenate the tibbles from the RDS files into a single tibble.\\n3. Pivot the tibble wider on the 'metric' column.\\n4. Compute the mCpG value using the formula mCpG = numCs / coverage, ensuring to drop rows where coverage is 0.\\n5. Group the data by 'sample' and 'chr' and calculate the mean mCpG per group.\\n6. Write the resulting data to 'output/mean_mcpg_split.tsv' using readr::write_tsv.\\n7. Verify the existence of the output file and submit the task as done.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (512 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_vHfFxxjEUPV3DubDJmV0eohg"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_ys7QDwRjeX4PBq8KYuB4uQXh", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(tibble); library(readr); library(dplyr); library(tidyr);\\n\\n# Load RDS files\\nrds_files <- list.files('input', pattern = 'mku.rds', full.names = TRUE)\\n\\n# Read and concatenate tibbles\\nall_data <- bind_rows(lapply(rds_files, readRDS))\\n\\n# Pivot wider on 'metric'\\nwider_data <- pivot_wider(all_data, names_from = metric, values_from = value)\\n\\n# Compute mCpG and filter\\nwider_data <- wider_data %>% mutate(mCpG = numCs / coverage) %>% filter(coverage != 0)\\n\\n# Group by 'sample' and 'chr' and calculate mean mCpG\\nmean_mcpg <- wider_data %>% group_by(sample, chr) %>% summarize(mean_mCpG = mean(mCpG, na.rm = TRUE))\\n\\n# Write to TSV\\nwrite_tsv(mean_mcpg, 'output/mean_mcpg_split.tsv')\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}, {"id": "call_gfjSjymYFzqPtVZYuykbaCK3", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"Note\": \"Executed R script to process RDS files and generate output TSV.\"}", "name": "check_progress"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\n\nAttaching package: \u2018dplyr\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    filter, lag\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    intersect, setdiff, setequal, union\n\nLoading required namespace: methylKit\nError:\n! Can't slice a scalar\nBacktrace:\n    \u2586\n 1. \u251c\u2500dply